<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 16 at 7:24PM MDT  by NWS Pocatello</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central Bear
Lake County through 800 PM MDT...
At 722 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northeast of Bear Lake Idaho Portion, moving northeast at 45
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Strong winds and rough waves on area lakes will create
hazardous conditions for small craft. Gusty winds could
knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Bear Lake Idaho Portion, Saint Charles and Fish Haven.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
